## New Project: stash
- **Replaces:** patrickmn/go-cache (Go, 7,109 importers, 8,804 stars)
- **Why:** Last release v2.1.0 Oct 2017 (8+ years). Last meaningful commit Oct 2019. Single maintainer (patrickmn, 157/164 commits). 76 open issues, unreviewed PRs. Uses interface{} throughout (pre-generics). No eviction policies, no size limits, no sharding. No forks with traction (max 23 stars). Existing alternatives (ristretto, bigcache, ttlcache) serve different niches — none drop-in compatible.
- **Package:** github.com/agentine/stash (verified available on pkg.go.dev)
- **Improvements:** Generics (Cache[K,V]), LRU/LFU eviction, sharded concurrency, go-cache compat layer, functional options
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #655 (scaffolding), #656 (core cache), #657 (eviction), #658 (sharding+compat), #659 (tests)

